sch:rule.sch:report:
Please use 
                                    @target if you need to point to something into the current file (e.g. #h1)
                                    or to point to a resource external to the project (http://www.example.com). if you need to point to a mss, use @corresp

bibl in a mss list of
                                    references with a @type="external" must contain a pointer with
                                    @target cointaing a full uri to the resource

witness must always contain a
                                    @corresp pointing to a project xml:id of a manuscript or to an
                                    external resource (in which case you need to add a
                                    @type="external")

bibl in a mss list of
                                    references with a @type="external" must contain a pointer with
                                    @target cointaing a full uri to the resource

Attribute
                                    @type='foundation' is require for date into a note about an
                                    institution.

locus must have either an
                                    exact reference to a page with @target or a range indicated with
                                    @from and @to.
